HB 609 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Chassion
Abstract: Provides for the one-time exemption of fees for health records when veterans are
seeking disability benefits administered by the federal and state veterans affairs
departments and that healthcare providers may require reasonable documentation to
establish veteran status.
Proposed law provides for the one-time exemption of fees when veterans are requesting
health records for the sole purpose of disability benefits administered by the United States
Department of Veterans Affairs or the Louisiana Department of Veterans Affairs.
Proposed law provides that healthcare providers or custodians may require reasonable
documentation to establish veteran status and that the records request is made in connection
to a disability benefits claim.
(Adds R.S. 40:1165.1(D))
